    <div class="card-content">
      <p>Creating the perfect smoothie is about balancing flavors and nutrition. Use this foolproof formula to build your own custom creations:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Liquid (1-1.5 cups):</strong> Almond milk, oat milk, coconut water, regular milk, or just water.</li>
        <li><strong>Base/Fruit (1 cup):</strong> Frozen banana, berries, mango, pineapple, or peaches for texture and natural sweetness.</li>
        <li><strong>Greens (1 handful, optional but recommended):</strong> Spinach, kale, or Swiss chard for a nutrient boost without altering the taste much.</li>
        <li><strong>Protein (1 scoop/serving):</strong> Whey, plant-based protein powder, Greek yogurt, silken tofu, or cottage cheese.</li>
        <li><strong>Healthy Fat/Thickener (1-2 tbsp):</strong> Chia seeds, flaxseeds, hemp hearts, peanut butter, almond butter, or avocado.</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="formula-highlight">
        Liquid + Base/Fruit + Greens + Protein + Healthy Fat = Perfect Smoothie
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="guide-card">
    <div class="card-header">
      <h2>Ingredient Freezing Guide</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="card-content">
      <p>Freezing your ingredients is the secret to a thick, creamy smoothie without watering it down with ice.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Bananas:</strong> Peel, slice, and freeze on a baking sheet before transferring to a bag. Essential for creaminess.</li>
        <li><strong>Greens:</strong> Blend spinach or kale with a little water and freeze in ice cube trays for easy green cubes.</li>
        <li><strong>Avocado:</strong> Halve, pit, scoop out chunks, and freeze on a parchment-lined tray. Great banana alternative for creaminess.</li>
        <li><strong>Berries:</strong> Wash, dry thoroughly, and freeze in a single layer before bagging to prevent clumping.</li>
        <li><strong>Leftover Coffee:</strong> Freeze black coffee or espresso in ice cube trays for an instant iced coffee smoothie boost.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

